          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "1801e4f435fe_14",
          "href": null,
          "name": "012f",
          "text": "Generally, once the ball is rolling, these things don’t take all that long. Everyone knows an early adopter or two and pretty quickly the good news of the hot new thing goes from “hearing about” to “seeing” and “believing”. It took four years to get from the BlackBerry smartphone to the iPhone, and from the Rio to the iPod. If the trends hold, we really should expect to see (and hear) drones becoming as common as white earbuds and zombie pedestrians over the next few years.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 453,
              "href": "http://www.mirror.co.uk/news/weird-news/worlds-first-mobile-phone-walking-4261228",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 435,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "1801e4f435fe_15",
          "href": null,
          "name": "8b81",
          "text": "I intend to use mine to check the surf and get croissants from the bakery across the street. Or, even better, I’m going to connect my Oculus Rift to my drone camera and really get a birds eye view. What will you use yours for?",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
